Steps to install flask on Centos6:
===================================
wget  wget http://mirror-fpt-telecom.fpt.net/fedora/epel/6/i386/epel-release-6-8.noarch.rpm
sudo rpm -ivh epel-release-6-8.noarch.rpm 
sudo yum install python-pip
sudo pip install flask

Install flask on Ubuntu
=======================
Similar to Centos steps: 

sudo apt-get install python-pip
sudo pip install flask


Work with the Flask book examples
================================

Install the following flask extensions:

flask-script
flask-bootstrap
argparse
flask-wtf
flask-sqlalchemy
flask-migrate


To use this for CS535 project
=============================
See the comments in cs535.py file
to update DB and table names matching those
defined by ssl server files

